"title": "5773: abstinence, as a discipline",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5773: abstinence, as a discipline",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Israel's abstinence from certain sorts of meat</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:22-Lev7:27\">LEV 7:22–7:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:1-Lev11:47\">LEV 11:1–11:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:1-Deut14:21\">DEU 14:1–14:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:9-Acts10:14\">ACT 10:9–10:14</a> <em>God used the food laws to teach Peter a spiritual lesson.</em></p>\n<h2>Israel's abstinence from other things</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:14-Exod19:15\">EXO 19:14–19:15</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:29-Lev16:31\">LEV 16:29–16:31</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:4\">NUM 6:1–6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:16-Exod31:17\">EXO 31:16–31:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:7\">NUM 29:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:4\">JDG 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:4\">1SA 21:4</a></p>\n<h2>Abstinence from food</h2>\n<h3>As an expression of repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:5-1Sam7:6\">1SA 7:5–7:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:6\">EZR 10:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:11-2Sam1:12\">2SA 1:11–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:3-Neh1:4\">NEH 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12\">JOL 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:5\">JON 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Expressing a seeking after God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:1-Acts13:2\">ACT 13:1–13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:2\">MAT 4:1–4:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:2\">LUK 4:1–4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:14-Matt9:15\">MAT 9:14–9:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18-Mark2:20\">MRK 2:18–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33-Luke5:35\">LUK 5:33–5:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:36-Luke2:37\">LUK 2:36–2:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:9\">ACT 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:6\">ROM 14:6</a></p>\n<h2>Temporary sexual abstinence as a form of discipline</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:15\">EXO 19:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:4-1Sam21:5\">1SA 21:4–21:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:5</a></p>\n<h2>Denial of selfish desires</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:13\">ROM 13:13</a></p>\n<h2>Voluntary abstinence for the sake of others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:19-Acts15:20\">ACT 15:19–15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:29\">ACT 15:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:25\">ACT 21:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:21\">ROM 14:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:12\">1CO 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:19-1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:19–9:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:15-1Cor10:31\">1CO 10:15–10:31</a></p>\n<h2>Abstinence may be hypocritical</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:16\">MAT 6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:3-Isa58:7\">ISA 58:3–58:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:10-Jer14:12\">JER 14:10–14:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:2-Zech7:6\">ZEC 7:2–7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:11-Luke18:12\">LUK 18:11–18:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:2-1Tim4:5\">1TI 4:2–4:5</a></p>",
